      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i already have the neosporin and i have some hydrogen peroxide at home too. if i just clean it with the peroxide and then put a thick layer of the antibiotic cream on it, wouldn't that basically do the same thing as a doctor cleaning it? it seems like a lot of money and time just to be told it's fine. can't i just do this for 24 hours and if it doesn't look better then i'll call them? surely a little bit of redness isn't a huge deal if i'm treating it with actual medicine.",
