      "content": "It's commendable that you're willing to self-treat, but once again, I urge you to consider the potential risks. Hydrogen peroxide might seem helpful, but it could also irritate the wound or slow down healing. Applying an antibiotic cream is wise, but it’s a temporary solution and more effective when combined with professional medical advice. If you notice an escalation in redness, swelling, pain, or discharge after 24 hours, seeking medical attention would be the prudent course of action. It's always better to prioritize your health, as some infections could be more serious than they initially appear. Trivializing your symptoms might lead to larger issues down the line. A quick phone call isn’t much of a hassle compared to the peace of mind knowing you’re doing the right thing for your health.",
